{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01SNP15wpLxaTDJ88Vpr73Vx","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The error is interesting. The error message says \"Can't find a `node_ip_address.json` file from /tmp/ray/session_2026-06-16_01-10-44_193654_13.\" It seems like the ray-client pod already has a stale Ray session from a previous session and it's looking for local node address file rather than connecting to the external Ray cluster.\n\nThe error says \"A ray instance hasn't started. Did you do `ray start` or `ray.init` on this host?\" - this is because the client pod itself may have Ray already partially initialized or there's a stale session.\nI think the issue is that the client pod has a leftover Ray session from before the head node was deployed, and when we call `ray.init(address='ray-head:6379')`, it's trying to connect as a driver but the local raylet process is still looking for its node configuration file in the stale session directory. I need to look at the ray-client.yaml file to see what command it's actually executing.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1019,"cache_read_input_tokens":30889,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1019},"output_tokens":48,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a0c11190-b1db-46a9-8f4c-b6a2153a9178","uuid":"deaadbcc-74c1-4a76-ab30-ecd79ce798b2","request_id":"req_011Cc6brchPjhPs5jinYVa56"}
